# Code Explanation

### Initialize Pointer

```java
TreeNode current = root;
```

Starts traversal from the root.

---

### Traverse the Tree

```java
while(current != null)
```

Visit every node.

---

### Check Left Subtree

```java
if(current.left != null)
```

Only rearrange pointers if a left subtree exists.

---

### Find Rightmost Node

```java
TreeNode predecessor = current.left;

while(predecessor.right != null){
    predecessor = predecessor.right;
}
```

Find the last node in the left subtree.

---

### Attach Original Right Subtree

```java
predecessor.right = current.right;
```

Prevents losing the original right subtree.

---

### Move Left Subtree

```java
current.right = current.left;
```

The left subtree becomes the new right subtree.

---

### Remove Left Pointer

```java
current.left = null;
```

The final linked list must use only right pointers.

---

### Move Forward

```java
current = current.right;
```

Continue processing the next node.

